Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.68,0:01:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0008,,{\fn华文楷体\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&\blur3}宇宙:另一个地球{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.54,0:00:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}创世之初 冥冥之中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the beginning, there was darkness...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.92,0:00:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}随着轰的一声{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and then, bang...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.08,0:00:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}诞生了无限膨胀的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}giving birth to an endless expanding existence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.30,0:00:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}时间 空间和物质{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of time, space, and matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.88,0:00:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}现在 所见超乎我们的想象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Now, see further than we've ever imagined...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.22,0:00:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}超越了我们生存的限制{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}beyond the limits of our existence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.34,0:00:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这个空间我们称之为"宇宙"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in a place we call "The Universe."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.56,0:00:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们孤独吗?{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Are we alone...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.60,0:00:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}抑或宇宙的某处存在着另一颗类地行星呢?{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or is there another Earth-Like planet somewhere in the universe?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.27,0:00:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们一直对我们的下一代有一个奇妙的目标{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We have a fantastic goal yet for the next generation...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.77,0:00:32.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那就是找到让我们缅怀老家的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which is to find planets that remind us of home.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.74,0:00:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我相信我们有望{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}I believe we're right on the brink...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.82,0:00:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}利用科技的能力来回答这个问题{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of having the technological capability to actually answer the question...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.28,0:00:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那是人类过去2000年以来一直在扪心自问的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that humanity has been asking itself for the last 2,000 years.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.00,0:00:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}另一个地球可能就近在离我们最近的太阳系里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Another Earth could be as close as our nearest star system.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.33,0:00:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们就站在能发现这些行星的门槛上了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We're right on the threshold...of being able to find these planets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.17,0:00:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有可能是被怪异的太阳所扭曲的地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}There could be twisted Earths under bizarre suns.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.85,0:01:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们能否发现那些地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Can we find these other Earths as they float, hidden...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.68,0:01:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果它们游荡 隐藏在宇宙数十亿颗恒星 数万亿颗行星中呢?{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in the billions of stars and trillions of planets of the universe?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙间存在另一颗地球吗?{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Is there another Earth in the universe?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.34,0:01:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这或许是最古老的想法之一{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's perhaps one of the oldest ideas...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.59,0:01:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}自打人类能注视星空以来就耿耿于怀{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}since mankind was able to look up at the stars and wonder.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.47,0:01:42.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}当年人们围坐在篝火旁{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Back when people were sitting around their campfires...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.68,0:01:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}仰望群星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and looking up at the stars...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.72,0:01:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}把它们想象成篝火{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and imagining them as other campfires...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.43,0:01:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其它种族围坐在旁边{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}with other tribes around them.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.06,0:01:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}究竟什么是我们所指的另一个地球呢?{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}What exactly do we mean by another Earth?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.40,0:01:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它应该能维持类地生命{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It should support Earth-Like life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.53,0:02:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}归结一下 生命需要三个最基本的东西才能生存{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When you boil it down, life needs three very basic things to exist.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.82,0:02:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它需要某种液态介质来进行化学反应{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It needs a liquid medium of some sort to do its chemical reactions in...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.25,0:02:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们认为水是最合适的液态介质{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and we think water is the most likely liquid medium.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.75,0:02:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它在宇宙间相当普遍{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's pretty prevalent in the universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.92,0:02:14.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们还需要找到生命的基本组成部分{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We also need to look for the basic building blocks of life...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.17,0:02:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}可以帮助组成生命的分子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the molecules that can help to put life together...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.42,0:02:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你的DNA里的磷{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the phosphorus in your DNA.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.68,0:02:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们需要有能源{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And we need to have an energy source.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.68,0:02:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}结果就是类地行星上有水{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It turns out that a terrestrial planet that has water on it...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.02,0:02:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}几乎具备我们所需的所有这些东西{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}pretty much has all of those things we need.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.56,0:02:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}并非所有能维持类地生命的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Not all planets capable of supporting Earth-Like life...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.06,0:02:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}都必须是我们地球的拷贝不走样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}would have to be carbon copies of our own Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.90,0:02:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此你可以将它看作是一系列不同类型的房子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So you can think of it like a series of different types of houses.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.16,0:02:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}假如你来到一座城市 举个例子 会有豪宅{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If you go into a city, for example, there will be grand mansions...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.07,0:02:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}会有较小的 较适中的二居室小住宅{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and there will be smaller, more modest little two-bedroom homes...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.12,0:02:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}会有市民公寓以及摩天大楼{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and there will be city studios and skyscrapers...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.71,0:02:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}等等之类{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and so on and so forth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.54,0:02:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}都住满了人{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}All of these house people.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.88,0:02:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所有这些都有助于安顿生命{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}All of these can help house life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.34,0:02:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以我们在琢磨{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And so we think about that...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.38,0:02:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们走进宇宙所看到的情形{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}when we go out into the universe looking.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.59,0:02:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们将要看看各种不同种类的房子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We're going to be looking for houses of all different kinds...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.84,0:03:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}敞开思绪 看看什么能维持生命{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and keeping our minds open as to what could support life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.48,0:03:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}天文学家已经发现了300多颗日外行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Astronomers have found over 300 exoplanets...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.90,0:03:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}也就是 我们太阳系外的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that is, planets outside our solar system.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.61,0:03:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}绝大多数是气体巨星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The vast majority are gas giants...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.74,0:03:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其发现要比我们地球这样的类地行星来得容易{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which are easier to find than small terrestrial planets like our Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.37,0:03:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}为了打造分析那些类地行星的仪器{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}To build instruments to analyze those Earth-like planets...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.12,0:03:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们必须提前预计到{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we have to anticipate ahead of time...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.58,0:03:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}类地行星大气层里有可能有何种化学物质{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}what the chemicals might be in that Earth-like atmosphere.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.67,0:03:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}基于那个原因 我们需要理论 需要模型{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}For that reason, we need theory, we need models.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.34,0:03:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}维多利亚.梅道斯埋头于行星建模的专研{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Victoria Meadows is in the planet modeling business.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.59,0:03:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}她领导的虚拟行星实验室{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}She heads up the Virtual Planet Laboratory...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.09,0:03:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}坐落在西雅图的华盛顿大学{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}at Seattle's University of Washington.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.89,0:03:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其团队 分布在全国各地的机构里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The group, spread across institutions around the country...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.56,0:03:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}构建着未探索宇宙间可能存在的世界{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}builds worlds that may exist in the yet unexplored universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.73,0:03:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}虚拟行星实验室让我们去模拟{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Virtual Planetary Laboratory allows us to simulate...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.98,0:04:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太空中的行星的模样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}what planets might look like from space...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其环境究竟是怎么回事{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and what their environments might be like...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.99,0:04:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}实际上是超前去探索{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in advance of actually discovering these things...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.37,0:04:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙间的这些东西{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}out there in the universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.70,0:04:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以说 它让我们去探索行星可能的模样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So it allows us to explore what planets might be like.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.83,0:04:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在虚拟行星实验室里 构建奇幻世界{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the Virtual Planet Lab, fantastic worlds can be built...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.83,0:04:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如科幻小说家那样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}like a science fiction novelist...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.63,0:04:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}将超级计算机作为写作搭档{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}with a supercomputer as a writing partner.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们可以拿上地球之类的东西{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So we can take something that's like the Earth...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.38,0:04:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不过我们会取走太阳{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but we rip away the Sun, and we replace it...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:29.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}用不同大小和温度的恒星来取代它{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}with a star of different size and temperature.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.43,0:04:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以我们在虚拟行星实验室里所做的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So what we've done with the Virtual Planetary Laboratory...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.43,0:04:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就是模拟开始就表现为地球类的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is modeled planets that started out as Earth-like...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.85,0:04:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}将它们围绕着恒星 其温度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and put them around stars that were much hotter...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.02,0:04:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其紫外线的强度都要比我们的太阳来得厉害{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}with much stronger UV radiation, for example, than our own Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.69,0:04:46.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些模型可以产生千奇百怪的候补地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The models can produce bizarre alternate Earths...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.11,0:04:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}生长的植物有鲜红的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}filled with plants that are bright red...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.12,0:04:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}橙色的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}orange...{\r}
